write_name_mapping(25.10)                            write_name_mapping(25.10)

Name
       write_name_mapping  -  Writes  or updates the initial netlist key point
       names and corresponding current netlist key point names to a file

Syntax
       write_name_mapping

       [-help]

       [-bbox_pins]

       [-hierarchical]

       [-map_pins {input output all}]

       [-pin_polarity]

       [-enable_one_to_one_mapping |-report_power_format]

       [-skip_clock_gate]

       [-updated_only]

       {<output_filename>  |  [[-output  <output_directory>]  -prefix   <file-
       name_prefix>]}

       [-hdl     |     -initial     |    [-input_mapping_file    <mapping_file
       >[-print_deleted][-include_new_iterms ]]]

       Writes or updates the initial netlist key point names and corresponding
       current netlist key point names to a file. Mapping file consists of pin
       mapping information of all changes done during the flow  (between  com-
       parison points) including polarity changes .

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each write_name_mapping parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man write_name_mapping

       -bbox_pins
              Prints the pins of bbox in the output mapping  file  instead  of
              inst names.

              * Prints bbox input pins if -map_pins {input} is specified.

              * Prints bbox output pins if -map_pins {output} is specified.

              * Prints both input and output pins if -map_pins {all} is speci-
                fied.

       -enable_one_to_one_mapping
              When the value is set as true, only one of the clones is printed
              in the mapping file.

       <output_filename>
              Specifies the name of the output mapping file.

       -hdl   Enables the generation of name mapping from current names to the
              names defined by the 'hdl_name' attribute. This will be used for
              power analysis.

       -hierarchical
              Specify if write out other post boundary optimizations mapping

       -initial
              Enables  the  generation  of  name mapping from current names to
              names defined by the 'initial_name' attribute.

              This will be used for  verification  of  initial  input  netlist
              (post-synthesis)  to  any other netlist generated during the In-
              novus flow.  The  write_do_lec  command  in  Innovus  will  call
              write_name_mapping  -initial  so  that Conformal LEC do file and
              name mapping file are generated in one shot. The  do  file  will
              source  the name mapping file to facilitate key point mapping in
              LEC.

       -include_new_iterms
              When the value is set as true, the output  mapping  file  writes
              the  updated iterms as well as  the new iterms that exist in In-
              novus but not in the input mapping file.

       -input_mapping_file <mapping_file>
              When provided Tool will read existing mapping file and write out
              updated mapping file.

       -map_pins {input output all}
              Specify type of pins to write out.

              Default: input

       -output <output_directory>
              Specify output directory

       -pin_polarity
              Specify if write out polarity information

       -prefix <filename_prefix>
              Used for file name prefix

       -print_deleted
              When -print_deleted is specified  the  mapping  file  will  also
              print deleted instances.

       -report_power_format
              Specify if write out 1Pass power replay format.

       -skip_clock_gate
              Filters out ICGs that are not in RTL.

              If  you  set  -skip_clock_gate to true with -hdl, the tool skips
              the  clock  gate  pins  except  the  pins  with   hdl_name.   If
              -skip_clock_gate  is  set to true and -hdl is not specified, the
              tool skips all clock gate pins.

       -updated_only
              Skips printing the pin that does not have any change/update dur-
              ing optimizations/flow.

